Ah, a fellow custom layout user! Swedish Dvorak with programming tweaks - that's a special kind of keyboard masochism I can respect 

So `ctrl-?` is probably not the most ergonomic choice for you. Looking at your keymap, you could add more comfortable bindings for the Claude panel. Maybe something like:

```json
{
    "context": "Workspace",
    "bindings": {
        "ctrl-": "agent::ToggleFocus",  // or whatever key is comfortable
        "ctrl-": "agent::ToggleFocus",  // scandinavian keys ftw
    }
},
{
    "context": "Editor && vim_mode == normal", 
    "bindings": {
        "space a": "agent::ToggleFocus",  // 'a' for AI/agent
        ", c": "agent::ToggleFocus",  // comma as leader alternative
    }
}
```

The struggle of non-US layouts with programming tools is real. Half the shortcuts assume you have easy access to characters that require finger gymnastics on Nordic keyboards!

